 and courageous, Lingis's writing has generated intense interest and debate among gender and cultural theorists as well as philosophers, and Dangerous Emotions is certain to introduce his work to an ever broader circle of readers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEmotions (Philosophy). 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aLingis, Alphonso, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022559640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092577940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520925779423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520925779/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles